JOHANNESBURG - The markets, currency, ratings agencies and Chamber of Mines all did not react well to Mineral Resources Minister, Mosebenzi Zwane's new mining charter. But President Jacob Zuma has brushed aside criticics who are concerned about the impact the move could have on jobs in the sector. The charter has has increased the black ownership target  to 30%. READ: Minister chased from mining charter meeting So how will this affect investors in the long-term? eNA's Jeremy Maggs speaks to Chief Economist at Standard Chartered Bank, Razia Khan about this​. eNCA